  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Human Resource Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintain and update employee records and HR databases.</li>\n  <li>Prepare offer letters, contracts, and coordinate onboarding to create a great first impression for new hires.</li>\n  <li>Handle uniform issuance administration.</li>\n  <li>Manage job postings and applicant tracking on various job portals, including MyCareersFuture, LinkedIn, JobStreet, FastJobs, etc.</li>\n  <li>Ensure job advertisements are up-to-date and aligned with the company's hiring needs.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and respond to candidate applications and inquiries on these platforms.</li>\n  <li>Handle MOM Work Pass applications, renewals, and cancellations.</li>\n  <li>Checking our MOM quota</li>\n  <li>Stay updated with Singapore employment laws and ensure all HR practices comply with legal requirements.</li>\n  <li>Provide guidance on employment law and regulatory changes to the HR team and management.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and present recruitment reports and metrics to management.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for the follow-up &amp; execution of all HR related processes e.g. hiring, onboarding, confirmation, resignations, transfers, staff requests etc.</li>\n  <li>Develop and implement effective recruitment strategies to attract top talent.</li>\n  <li>Conduct initial screenings and interviews to shortlist qualified candidates.</li>\n  <li>Manage both pantry and office supplies</li>\n  <li>Other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the management</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or a related field.</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of experience in HR administration or shared services.</li>\n  <li>A solid grasp of Singapore employment laws and experience with work pass processes.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in HR software and Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, PowerPoint).</li>\n</ul>",
